<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="327" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1647,1962]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1719,1745]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Discussion.</emphasis>
Although this species is known only from one incomplete pygidium, enough is preserved to show that it has an unusually deeply curved, elongate profile, relatively narrow axis and prominent ribs. 
<bibRefCitation author="Reed, F. R. C." box="[1294,1436,1755,1782]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref46807" refString="Reed, F. R. C. (1915) Supplementary Memoir on new Ordovician and Silurian fossils from the Northern Shan States. Palaeontologia Indica, New Series 6, 1 - 98." type="book chapter" year="1915">Reed (1915)</bibRefCitation>
compared this specimen with the pygidium of 
<taxonomicName box="[668,797,1791,1817]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Megalaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[668,797,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Megalaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaanuson" authorityYear="1956" box="[868,1002,1792,1817]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Megistaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[868,1002,1792,1817]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Megistaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) a diverse genus that is confined to the Baltic palaeoplate in the Ordovician. A more plausible comparison is with 
<emphasis box="[992,1176,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobayashi" authorityYear="1934" box="[992,1173,1827,1853]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Dolerobasilicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dolerobasilicus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1361,1433,1828,1854]" name="South Korea" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Korea</collectingCountry>
. Revision of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kobayashi 1934" authorityName="Kobayashi" authorityYear="1934" box="[290,787,1863,1889]" class="Trilobita" family="Asaphidae" genus="Dolerobasilicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Asaphida" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yokusensis">
<emphasis box="[290,596,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Dolerobasilicus yokusensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kobayashi, T." box="[604,787,1863,1889]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" pagination="521 - 585" refId="ref44978" refString="Kobayashi, T. (1934) The Cambro-Ordovician formations and faunas of South Chosen Palaeontology, part 2. Lower Ordovician faunas. Journal of the Faculty of Science, Imperial University of Japan, Tokyo, Section II, 3 (9), 521 - 585." type="journal article" year="1934">Kobayashi 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, D. C. &amp; Choi, D. K." box="[831,1048,1863,1890]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" pagination="167 - 183" refId="ref45323" refString="Lee, D. C. &amp; Choi, D. K. (1988) Reappraisal of the Middle Ordovician trilobites from the Jingunsan Formation, Korea. Journal of the Geological Society of Korea, 28, 167 - 183." type="journal article" year="1988">Lee &amp; Choi (1988)</bibRefCitation>
includes several pygidia (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, D. C. &amp; Choi, D. K." pageId="26" pageNumber="327" pagination="167 - 183" refId="ref45323" refString="Lee, D. C. &amp; Choi, D. K. (1988) Reappraisal of the Middle Ordovician trilobites from the Jingunsan Formation, Korea. Journal of the Geological Society of Korea, 28, 167 - 183." type="journal article" year="1988">Lee &amp; Choi, 1988</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 1, fig. 9) with similar elongate form and about ten ribs. While the evidence is incomplete, it is sufficient to suggest the presence of this genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[708,819,1936,1962]" name="Myanmar" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
